data.title: 30 Best Bosnian Actresses of All Time
data.meta_description: List of 30 Best Bosnian Actresses of All Time. (2016.)
data.text:
Marija Pikic was born on 17 December 1989 in Trebinje, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for Meso (2018), Balada (2022) and Djeca - Kinder von Sarajevo (2012).

Nada Djurevska was born on 8 January 1952 in Skoplje, Macedonia, Yugoslavia. She was an actress, known for Od zlata jabuka (1986), Obrana i zastita (2013) and Viza za buducnost (2002). She died on 13 September 2017 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina.

Jasna Beri was born on 2 January 1954 in Zenica, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for In the Land of Blood and Honey (2011), Pecat (2008) and Cirkus Columbia (2010).

Born in Sarajevo, 2nd of December 1991. Her acting career started in 2005 when chosen to play the role of Sara in "Grbavica" (directed by Jasmila Zbanic, winner of the Golden Bear 2006.) It was her first acting experience and she continues to do acting in Bosnia, Slovenia, Croatia, Holland, Austria and Germany.

Jasna Diklic was born on 8 March 1946 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina. She is an actress, known for Back Up, Ne diraj mi mamu (2018) and Paviljon.

Jasna Zalica was born in 1968 in Sarajevo, Bosnia. She is an actress, known for Takva su pravila (2014), Pink Elephant (2017) and Znam Kako Dises (2023).

Emina Minka Muftic was born on 15 June 1961 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for Quo vadis, Aida? (2020), Twice Born - Was vom Leben übrig bleibt (2012) and Game of Thrones: Das Lied von Eis und Feuer (2011).

Zana Marjanovic was born on 31 May 1983 in Sarajevo, Yugoslavia [now Bosnia and Herzegovina]. She is an actress and producer, known for In the Land of Blood and Honey (2011), A Rose in Winter (2018) and Broken (2012). She has been married to Emir Kapetanovic since 2 March 2014. They have two children.

Vedrana Bozinovic was born on 25 April 1976 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress and writer, known for Im Fadenkreuz - Allein gegen alle (2001), Ostrom (2018) and Kotlina (2022). She was previously married to Aleksandar Seksan.

Faketa Salihbegovic was born on 14 August 1962 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for Ja, Chef (2021), Body Complete (2012) and Tata i zetovi (2006). She is married to Mugdim Avdagic. They have two children.

Snezana Vidovic was born on 29 November 1980 in Zenica, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for Hunting Party - Wenn der Jäger zum Gejagten wird (2007), Paviljon and Tod in Sarajevo (2016).

Jelena Kordic Kuret was born on 28 February 1979 in Sarajevo, Yugoslavia [now Bosnia and Hercegovina]. She is an actress, known for The Happiest Man in the World (2022), Quo vadis, Aida? (2020) and Ljeto u zlatnoj dolini (2003).

Alma Terzic was born on 11 July 1987 in Zenica, Yugoslavia [now Bosnia and Herzegovina]. She is an actress, known for In the Land of Blood and Honey (2011), Seref Meselesi (2014) and Turkish Ice Cream - Türk Isi Dondurma (2019).

Vanessa Glodjo was born on 8 June 1974 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for In the Land of Blood and Honey (2011), Das Leben ist ein Wunder (2004) and Crna hronika (2004).

Sadzida Setic was born on 6 March 1968 in Sarajevo, Yugoslavia [now Bosnia and Herzegovina]. She is an actress, known for Min faster i Sarajevo (2016), Body Complete (2012) and Belvedere (2010).

Alena Dzebo was born on 1 April 1978 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress and assistant director, known for Sabina K. (2015), Alenino putovanje (2008) and Import (2016).

Tatjana Sojic was born on 9 April 1964 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for Lud, zbunjen, normalan (2007), Crna hronika (2004) and 60 Minuten (2024).

Sanela Pepeljak was born on 11 June 1974 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for Gori vatra (2003), Ljeto u zlatnoj dolini (2003) and Lazni svjedok (2016).

Gordana Milinovic was born on 11 February 1944 in Kovilje, Serbia, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for Zene, ljudi i ostalo (1999), So (1973) and 32. decembar (2009).

Sladjana Zrnic was born on 22 February 1974 in Banja Luka, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for Hotel Balkan (2020), Last Perspective (2015) and Schwarze Sonne (2017).

Maja Izetbegovic was born on 20 February 1985 in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for TV teatar (1956), Hotel Pula (2023) and Regained Memory (2018).

Nikolina Friganovic was born on 21 February 1978 in Banja Luka, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Yugoslavia. She is an actress, known for Dara iz Jasenovca (2020), Last Perspective (2015) and Pecat (2008).

Irena Mulamuhic was born in 1945 in Bosanski Brod, Yugoslavia [now Bosnia and Herzegovina]. She is an actress, known for In the Land of Blood and Honey (2011), Quo vadis, Aida? (2020) and Tale (1977).
